Assignment:

Respond to one of the two following prompts:

Darwin wrote that: "Man still bears in his bodily frame the indelible stamp of his lowly origin." Compare Darwin's view of the persistent effects of the past with at least one other
writer covered so far in the course (please try to write about someone you haven't written about in the previous assignments).

OR

Describe how Darwin makes use of the intellectual traditions of utilitarianism and romanticism in his work. Compare this use to how another thinker makes use of the past in his or
her own work (this can be anyone covered so far in the course, but please try to write about someone you haven't written about in the previous assignments).
